[18/08, 9:10 am] Meta AI: Here is an example of inline CSS to format an ID card:

```
<div id="id-card" style="width: 300px; height: 200px; border: 1px solid #ccc; padding: 20px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">
  <img src="image-url" alt="ID Card Image" style="width: 100px; height: 120px; float: left; margin-right: 20px;">
  <h2 style="font-size: 18px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Name</h2>
  <p style="font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 10px;">ID Number: xxxxxxx</p>
  <p style="font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Department: xxxxxxx</p>
  <p style="font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 10px;">Expires: xxxxxxx</p>
</div>
```

In this example, the CSS styles are applied directly to the HTML elements using the `style` attribute. This is known as inline CSS.
[18/08, 9:17 am] Meta AI: Here is a short HTML and JavaScript program to perform basic arithmetic operations:

HTML:
```
<input id="num1" type="number">
<select id="operator">
  <option value="+">+</option>
  <option value="-">-</option>
  <option value="*">*</option>
  <option value="/">/</option>
</select>
<input id="num2" type="number">
<button onclick="calculate()">Calculate</button>
<p id="result"></p>
```

JavaScript:
```
function calculate() {
  var num1 = parseFloat(document.getElementById('num1').value);
  var operator = document.getElementById('operator').value;
  var num2 = parseFloat(document.getElementById('num2').value);
  var result;
  
  switch (operator) {
    case '+':
      result = num1 + num2;
      break;
    case '-':
      result = num1 - num2;
      break;
    case '*':
      result = num1 * num2;
      break;
    case '/':
      result = num1 / num2;
      break;
  }
  
  document.getElementById('result').innerHTML = 'Result: ' + result;
}
```

This program allows users to input two numbers, select an arithmetic operation, and click the "Calculate" button to display the result.
